Programmer view: ``struc = head(file)``: Command output
``filename:`` -- Name of the file containing the object
``filepath:``  -- path to the file containing the object
``title:``  -- Titile to be displayed on image
``alatt:`` -- 3-element array of lattice parameter
``angdeg:`` -- 3-element array of lattice angle
``offset:`` -- Image offset from point ``[0,0,0,0]`` in :math:`hklE`
``u_to_rlu:`` -- 4x4 matrix used for conversion from pixel to image coorinate system
``ulen:`` -- scales for conversion from pixel to image coordinate system
``label:`` -- axis labels
``iax:``  -- what directions of full 4-dimensional dataset are integrated
``iint:`` -- ``[2xnumel(iax)]`` array of integration ranges (parts of img_range)
``pax`` -- what direction of full 4-dim dataset is binned
``p:`` -- ``numel(pax)`` cellarray of  binning ranges for each binned axis
``dax:`` -- order of displaying axis  among
``img_range:`` -- Ranges of the image dimensions incliding integrated and binned dimensions
``dimensions:`` -- Number of image dimensions
``creation_date:`` -- Date the ``sqw`` object was created. Valid for Horace-4 objects only. Empty for previous versions
``npixels:`` -- Number of pixels (neutron events) stored in dataset
``num_contrib_files:`` -- Number of source files (runs) contributed into the dataset
``data_range:`` -- 2x9 array of min/max ranges of Pixel data

Scientific view: ``head(file);``: Object is stored in Horace-2 format file
Programmer view: ``struc = head(file)``: ``faccess_version:`` -- version of class used to access data. Usually corresponds to Horace version
